{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_10","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,260p' prompts/iphone-app-factory/architecture-candidate.md\"","aggregated_output":"# Independent Architecture Candidate\n\nRead:\n\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec.md`\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/definition-of-done.md`\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/quality-bar.json`\n- SwiftAIBoilerplatePro docs if available in the app repo or GitHub.\n\nCreate an architecture plan that extends SwiftAIBoilerplatePro instead of rebuilding it.\n\nCover:\n\n- modules/packages to keep unchanged\n- modules/packages to adapt\n- modules/packages to remove only if justified\n- CompositionRoot changes\n- DesignSystem usage\n- data/repository/client plan\n- ViewModel boundaries\n- Swift 6 concurrency risks\n- test plan\n- Appium exploratory harness plan\n- GitHub macOS CI plan\n\nWrite the architecture candidate in your response with a clear model identity.\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_9","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc 'rg -n \"architecture candidate|candidate architecture|architecture\" .workflow/iphone-app-factory prompts/iphone-app-factory | head -n 80'","aggregated_output":"prompts/iphone-app-factory/simplification.md:6:- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture.md`\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/definition-of-done.md:31:- [ ] Final review fanout signs off product fidelity, iOS architecture, security/privacy, code quality, QA evidence, and release readiness.\nprompts/iphone-app-factory/review-ios-architecture.md:3:Review the generated app against `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture.md`, the boilerplate docs, and Swift 6 expectations.\nprompts/iphone-app-factory/review-ios-architecture.md:5:Write `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/reviews/ios-architecture.md`.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/research-synthesis.md:84:- Distinct trust model: reliability telemetry and mission-safe fallback architecture.\nprompts/iphone-app-factory/review-implementation-tests.md:3:Read the spec, definition of done, architecture, phase evidence, and app code.\nprompts/iphone-app-factory/review-implementation-security.md:3:Read the spec, architecture, phase evidence, app code, configs, scripts, and generated CI.\nprompts/iphone-app-factory/review-implementation-correctness.md:7:- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture.md`\nprompts/iphone-app-factory/review-implementation-boilerplate.md:3:Read the spec, architecture, ADR, phase evidence, and app code.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/evals/promptfoo-output.json:9:        \"raw\": \"Evaluate whether this iPhone App Factory prompt suite is strong enough for overnight agentic app generation.\\n\\nPrompt registry:\\n{{prompt_registry}}\\n\\nGolden cases:\\n{{golden_cases}}\\n\\nRepresentative prompts:\\nSPEC_CONSENSUS:\\n{{spec_consensus}}\\n\\nARCHITECTURE:\\n{{architecture_consensus}}\\n\\nIMPLEMENT_INTEGRATION:\\n{{implement_integration}}\\n\\nAI_UI_EXPLORER:\\n{{ai_ui_explorer}}\\n\\nFINAL_CONSENSUS:\\n{{final_consensus}}\\n\\nReturn valid JSON only, no markdown fences:\\n{\\\"verdict\\\":\\\"APPROVE\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.0,\\\"covered\\\":[\\\"spec_lab\\\",\\\"boilerplate_reuse\\\",\\\"ios_quality\\\",\\\"appium_qa\\\",\\\"mobbin_safety\\\",\\\"release_hardening\\\"],\\\"gaps\\\":[]}\\n\",\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/evals/promptfoo-output.json:10:        \"label\": \"Evaluate whether this iPhone App Factory prompt suite is strong enough for overnight agentic app generation.\\n\\nPrompt registry:\\n{{prompt_registry}}\\n\\nGolden cases:\\n{{golden_cases}}\\n\\nRepresentative prompts:\\nSPEC_CONSENSUS:\\n{{spec_consensus}}\\n\\nARCHITECTURE:\\n{{architecture_consensus}}\\n\\nIMPLEMENT_INTEGRATION:\\n{{implement_integration}}\\n\\nAI_UI_EXPLORER:\\n{{ai_ui_explorer}}\\n\\nFINAL_CONSENSUS:\\n{{final_consensus}}\\n\\nReturn valid JSON only, no markdown fences:\\n{\\\"verdict\\\":\\\"APPROVE\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.0,\\\"covered\\\":[\\\"spec_lab\\\",\\\"boilerplate_reuse\\\",\\\"ios_quality\\\",\\\"appium_qa\\\",\\\"mobbin_safety\\\",\\\"release_hardening\\\"],\\\"gaps\\\":[]}\\n\",\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/evals/promptfoo-output.json:108:                \"renderedGradingPrompt\": \"[{\\\"role\\\":\\\"system\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"You are grading output according to a user-specified rubric. If the statement in the rubric is true, then the output passes the test. You respond with a JSON object with this structure: {reason: string, pass: boolean, score: number}\\\\n\\\\nExamples:\\\\n\\\\n<Output>Hello world</Output>\\\\n<Rubric>Content contains a greeting</Rubric>\\\\n{\\\\\\\"reason\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"the content contains the word 'Hello'\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"pass\\\\\\\": true, \\\\\\\"score\\\\\\\": 1.0}\\\\n\\\\n<Output>Avast ye swabs, repel the invaders!</Output>\\\\n<Rubric>Does not speak like a pirate</Rubric>\\\\n{\\\\\\\"reason\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"'avast ye' is a common pirate term\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"pass\\\\\\\": false, \\\\\\\"score\\\\\\\": 0.0}\\\"},{\\\"role\\\":\\\"user\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"<Output>\\\\n# Evaluation: iPhone App Factory Prompt Suite\\\\n\\\\n## Overall Assessment: **STRONG BUT WITH CRITICAL GAPS** (7.2/10)\\\\n\\\\nThis is a well-architected prompt suite with excellent structural discipline, but it has **three blocking vulnerabilities** for overnight agentic execution.\\\\n\\\\n---\\\\n\\\\n## Strengths ✅\\\\n\\\\n| Category | Evidence |\\\\n|----------|----------|\\\\n| **Workflow coherence** | Clear stage progression (research → spec → architecture → implementation → review → release) |\\\\n| **Spec lab rigor** | Independent candidates + adversarial critique + red team + consensus pattern is sound |\\\\n| **Boilerplate enforcement** | Multiple checkpoints (spec, architecture, implementation, review) bias toward reuse |\\\\n| **Quality gates** | Explicit xcodebuild, SwiftLint, SwiftFormat, Qlty, Appium requirements |\\\\n| **Verdict discipline** | Binary APPROVED/REJECTED verdicts with blocking rules prevent ambiguous handoffs |\\\\n| **Secret handling intent** | \\\\\\\"Never print environment variables\\\\\\\" appears 6+ times |\\\\n\\\\n---\\\\n\\\\n## Critical Gaps ❌\\\\n\\\\n### 1. **Secret Handling is Underspecified** (BLOCKING)\\\\n\\\\n**Problem:**\\\\n- `research-design-patterns.md` must_include lists `MOBBIN_EMAIL`, `MOBBIN_PASSWORD` but no prompt shows *how* to use them safely\\\\n- `implement-foundation.md` mentions \\\\\\\"secrets\\\\\\\" but doesn't specify injection mechanism\\\\n- No prompt explicitly forbids `os.environ.dump()`, `print(os.environ)`, or credential logging in agent outputs\\\\n- No prompt specifies redaction rules for CI logs\\\\n\\\\n**Risk:** Overnight agent could leak credentials to stdout/logs during research or implementation phases.\\\\n\\\\n**Required fix:**\\\\n```yaml\\\\nmust_include: [\\\\n  \\\\\\\"never print environment variables\\\\\\\",\\\\n  \\\\\\\"use getenv() with redaction wrapper\\\\\\\",\\\\n  \\\\\\\"credential verification: true/false only\\\\\\\",\\\\n  \\\\\\\"no credential values in logs or reports\\\\\\\",\\\\n  \\\\\\\"sanitize all JSON outputs for secrets\\\\\\\"\\\\n]\\\\n```\\\\n\\\\n### 2. **Appium/XCUITest Evidence is Optional** (BLOCKING FOR OVERNIGHT)\\\\n\\\\n**Problem:**\\\\n- `ai-ui-explorer.md` says \\\\\\\"Do not mark the pass complete unless a real simulator/Appium run happened, **unless the workflow explicitly allows macOS deferral**\\\\\\\"\\\\n- `final-consensus.md` says \\\\\\\"If macOS/Xcode or Appium evidence is missing **and not explicitly deferred**, reject\\\\\\\"\\\\n- No prompt defines what \\\\\\\"explicitly deferred\\\\\\\" means or under what conditions it's acceptable\\\\n- Overnight execution on headless CI likely cannot run iOS simulator → creates escape hatch for skipping QA\\\\n\\\\n**Risk:** Agent defers Appium, skips real device testing, ships untested app.\\\\n\\\\n**Required fix:**\\\\n```yaml\\\\n# In final-consensus.md\\\\nRules:\\\\n  - Appium deferral only allowed if:\\\\n    1. Workflow input explicitly sets \\\\\\\"defer_appium: true\\\\\\\"\\\\n    2. A blocking issue prevents simulator setup (documented)\\\\n</Output>\\\\n<Rubric>\\\\nThe prompt suite should make quality reproducible across prompt registry, golden cases, adversarial review, deterministic gates, and final release criteria.\\\\n</Rubric>\\\"}]\"\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/evals/promptfoo-output.json:117:          \"raw\": \"Evaluate whether this iPhone App Factory prompt suite is strong enough for overnight agentic app generation.\\n\\nPrompt registry:\\n{\\n  \\\"workflow\\\": \\\"iphone-app-factory\\\",\\n  \\\"dataset_version\\\": \\\"iphone-app-factory-prompts-v1\\\",\\n  \\\"rubric_version\\\": \\\"iphone-app-factory-prompt-rubric-v1\\\",\\n  \\\"prompts\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/research-app-store.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"research\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"App Store\\\", \\\"reviews\\\", \\\"evidence quality\\\", \\\"do not invent\\\", \\\"never print environment variables\\\", \\\"environment dump commands\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/research-reddit.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"research\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"Reddit\\\", \\\"source links\\\", \\\"do not fabricate\\\", \\\"never print environment variables\\\", \\\"environment dump commands\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/research-competitors.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"research\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"competitor\\\", \\\"positioning\\\", \\\"evidence quality\\\", \\\"never print environment variables\\\", \\\"environment dump commands\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/research-design-patterns.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"design\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"Mobbin\\\", \\\"MOBBIN_EMAIL\\\", \\\"MOBBIN_PASSWORD\\\", \\\"not clone\\\", \\\"never print environment variables\\\", \\\"environment dump commands\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/synthesize-research.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"synthesis\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"jobs-to-be-done\\\", \\\"differentiation\\\", \\\"opportunity-matrix.json\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/spec-candidate.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"spec\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"independent\\\", \\\"Definition of Done\\\", \\\"Appium\\\", \\\"SwiftAIBoilerplatePro\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/spec-cross-critique.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"spec-review\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"adversarial\\\", \\\"contradictions\\\", \\\"testability gaps\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/spec-consensus.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"spec\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"Research Evidence\\\", \\\"Boilerplate Reuse\\\", \\\"Appium Exploratory QA\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/spec-red-team.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"spec-review\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"VERDICT: APPROVED\\\", \\\"VERDICT: REJECTED\\\", \\\"release criteria\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/architecture-candidate.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"architecture\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"extends SwiftAIBoilerplatePro\\\", \\\"CompositionRoot\\\", \\\"Appium\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/architecture-consensus.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"architecture\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"architecture.md\\\", \\\"adr.md\\\", \\\"Packages/Core\\\", \\\"CompositionRoot\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/boilerplate-setup.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"implementation\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"do not recreate\\\", \\\"AGENTS.md\\\", \\\"DISTRIBUTION_README.md\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/implement-foundation.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"implementation\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"BrandConfig\\\", \\\"secrets\\\", \\\"Appium exploratory\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/implement-core.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"implementation\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"repositories\\\", \\\"ViewModel\\\", \\\"unit tests\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/implement-interface.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"implementation\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"DesignSystem\\\", \\\"accessibility\\\", \\\"actual app experience\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/implement-integration.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"implementation\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"xcodebuild\\\", \\\"SwiftLint\\\", \\\"SwiftFormat\\\", \\\"Appium\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/verify-phase.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"verify\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"independently verify\\\", \\\"boilerplate conventions\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/review-implementation-correctness.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"code-review\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"correctness\\\", \\\"spec.md\\\", \\\"blocking\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/review-implementation-tests.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"code-review\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"tests\\\", \\\"xcodebuild\\\", \\\"Appium\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/review-implementation-security.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"code-review\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"security\\\", \\\"privacy\\\", \\\"secrets\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/review-implementation-boilerplate.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"code-review\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"SwiftAIBoilerplatePro\\\", \\\"boilerplate\\\", \\\"unnecessary rebuild\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/review-implementation-consensus.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"code-review\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"implementation-consensus.md\\\", \\\"VERDICT: APPROVED\\\", \\\"VERDICT: REJECTED\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/simplification.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"simplify\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"split Swift files\\\", \\\"400 lines\\\", \\\"do not remove quality gates\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/ai-ui-explorer.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"qa\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"tap every reachable\\\", \\\"reports/ios/appium-exploratory-report.json\\\", \\\"crashes\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/app-store-hardening.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"release\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"SwiftAI\\\", \\\"Boilerplate\\\", \\\"release strings audit: PASS\\\", \\\"Privacy\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/review-product-fidelity.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"final-review\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"spec.md\\\", \\\"research synthesis\\\", \\\"template-like\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/review-ios-architecture.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"final-review\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"architecture.md\\\", \\\"Swift 6\\\", \\\"CompositionRoot\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/review-security-privacy.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"final-review\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"Security\\\", \\\"Privacy\\\", \\\"hardcoded secrets\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/review-code-quality.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"final-review\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"SwiftLint\\\", \\\"SwiftFormat\\\", \\\"Qlty\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/review-release-readiness.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"final-review\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"iOS CI report\\\", \\\"TestFlight\\\", \\\"macOS/Xcode\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/review-qa-evidence.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"final-review\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"Appium\\\", \\\"button tap coverage\\\", \\\"crashes\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/final-consensus.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"final-review\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"VERDICT: APPROVED\\\", \\\"VERDICT: REJECTED\\\", \\\"boilerplate\\\"]\\n    }\\n  ]\\n}\\n\\nGolden cases:\\n{\\\"id\\\":\\\"spec-lab\\\",\\\"input\\\":\\\"The spec lab prompts should force independent candidates, adversarial critique, consensus, red team, and a testable Definition of Done.\\\",\\\"expected_quality\\\":[\\\"independent candidates\\\",\\\"adversarial critique\\\",\\\"consensus merge\\\",\\\"red team verdict\\\",\\\"testable Definition of Done\\\"]}\\n{\\\"id\\\":\\\"boilerplate-first\\\",\\\"input\\\":\\\"Implementation prompts should bias agents to extend SwiftAIBoilerplatePro instead of rebuilding auth, payments, AI, storage, networking, localization, settings, or design system.\\\",\\\"expected_quality\\\":[\\\"boilerplate reuse\\\",\\\"module boundaries\\\",\\\"CompositionRoot\\\",\\\"no platform rewrite\\\",\\\"App Store 4.3 awareness\\\"]}\\n{\\\"id\\\":\\\"ios-qa\\\",\\\"input\\\":\\\"Quality prompts should require macOS Xcode evidence, strict Swift lint/format/static checks, sensitive-value scanning, Appium/XCUITest exploratory clicking, and release string audits.\\\",\\\"expected_quality\\\":[\\\"xcodebuild build/test\\\",\\\"SwiftLint\\\",\\\"SwiftFormat\\\",\\\"Qlty\\\",\\\"sensitive scan\\\",\\\"Appium exploratory tapping\\\",\\\"release string audit\\\"]}\\n{\\\"id\\\":\\\"mobbin-safe\\\",\\\"input\\\":\\\"Design research prompts may use Mobbin credential env vars but should not leak credentials, clone screens, or copy assets.\\\",\\\"expected_quality\\\":[\\\"credential env vars\\\",\\\"no secret logging\\\",\\\"pattern abstraction\\\",\\\"no cloning\\\",\\\"Apple HIG or DesignSystem cross-check\\\"]}\\n\\nRepresentative prompts:\\nSPEC_CONSENSUS:\\n# Spec Consensus\\n\\nRead:\\n\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/research-synthesis.md`\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/opportunity-matrix.json`\\n- all spec candidate outputs in context\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec-cross-critique.md`\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/quality-bar.json`\\n\\nMerge the strongest ideas into one buildable spec.\\n\\nWrite:\\n\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec.md`\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/definition-of-done.md`\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec-consensus.md`\\n\\n`spec.md` must include these section headings exactly:\\n\\n- `# Product Spec`\\n- `## Research Evidence`\\n- `## User Journeys`\\n- `## MVP Scope`\\n- `## Boilerplate Reuse`\\n- `## Design Direction`\\n- `## Acceptance Criteria`\\n- `## Appium Exploratory QA`\\n- `## App Store Readiness`\\n- `## Definition of Done`\\n\\nThe Definition of Done must be checklist-based and testable.\\n\\nARCHITECTURE:\\n# Architecture And ADR Consensus\\n\\nRead:\\n\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec.md`\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/definition-of-done.md`\\n- all architecture candidates in context\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/quality-bar.json`\\n\\nWrite:\\n\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture.md`\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/adr.md`\\n\\nThe architecture must explicitly map the product to SwiftAIBoilerplatePro:\\n\\n- `SwiftAIBoilerplatePro.xcodeproj`\\n- `Config/App.xcconfig`\\n- `Packages/Core`\\n- `Packages/Networking`\\n- `Packages/Storage`\\n- `Packages/Auth`\\n- `Packages/Payments`\\n- `Packages/AI`\\n- `Packages/FeatureSettings`\\n- `Packages/Localization`\\n- `Packages/DesignSystem`\\n- `CompositionRoot`\\n\\nIf any module is removed, the ADR must explain dependency order and App Store 4.3 consequences.\\n\\nIMPLEMENT_INTEGRATION:\\n# Implement Integration Phase\\n\\nImplement only the integration and release-hardening phase in `{{ inputs.app_dir|default(\\\"apps/generated-iphone-app\\\") }}`.\\n\\nScope:\\n\\n- wire feature into CompositionRoot/AppShell\\n- complete tests and UI test fixtures\\n- complete `scripts/ci/ios-quality.sh`\\n- complete `.github/workflows/ios-quality.yml`\\n- complete Appium exploratory script\\n- generate `reports/ios/ios-quality-report.json` when quality checks pass\\n- generate `reports/ios/appium-exploratory-report.json` when Appium checks pass\\n- create release/readiness docs\\n\\nThe CI script must include xcodebuild build/test, SwiftLint, SwiftFormat, Qlty, secret scan, and App Store string audit.\\n\\nSecret handling is blocking: never print environment variables or credential values. CI and local scripts may verify that required secrets are present, but output must be redacted true/false status only.\\n\\nWrite `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/evidence/integration.md` with:\\n\\n- `Files changed`\\n- `Commands run`\\n- `Acceptance criteria`\\n- `Risks`\\n\\nAI_UI_EXPLORER:\\n# AI UI Explorer\\n\\nRun or complete the automated exploratory UI pass for `{{ inputs.app_dir|default(\\\"apps/generated-iphone-app\\\") }}`.\\n\\nThe target behavior is: launch the iOS app in simulator through Appium/XCUITest and tap every reachable enabled button/control across the MVP flows.\\n\\nThe explorer should:\\n\\n- record each screen source or screenshot\\n- identify buttons, tabs, cells, navigation controls, and primary actions\\n- tap controls breadth-first with a bounded depth\\n- recover with back/navigation when possible\\n- detect crashes, blank screens, stuck spinners, and unhandled error screens\\n- produce `reports/ios/appium-exploratory-report.json`\\n\\nThe report JSON must include:\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"ok\\\": true,\\n  \\\"buttons_tapped\\\": 0,\\n  \\\"screens_visited\\\": 0,\\n  \\\"crashes\\\": 0,\\n  \\\"failures\\\": 0,\\n  \\\"failures_detail\\\": []\\n}\\n```\\n\\nDo not mark the pass complete unless a real simulator/Appium run happened, unless the workflow explicitly allows macOS deferral.\\n\\nFINAL_CONSENSUS:\\n# Final Consensus Review\\n\\nRead:\\n\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec.md`\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/definition-of-done.md`\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/reviews/product-fidelity.md`\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/reviews/ios-architecture.md`\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/reviews/security-privacy.md`\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/reviews/code-quality.md`\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/reviews/release-readiness.md`\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/reviews/qa-evidence.md`\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/quality-contract-gate.json`\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/ios-ci-gate.json`\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/appium-gate.json`\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/app-store-hardening-gate.json`\\n\\nMerge the review fanout into a final release decision.\\n\\nRules:\\n\\n- If any reviewer finds a blocking issue, reject.\\n- If macOS/Xcode or Appium evidence is missing and not explicitly deferred, reject.\\n- If the app does not use the boilerplate substantially, reject.\\n- If App Store 4.3 hardening did not pass, reject.\\n\\nWrite `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/final-consensus.md` with:\\n\\n- reviewer agreement/disagreement\\n- blocking issues\\n- remaining deferred items\\n- release handoff notes\\n\\nEnd with exactly one verdict line:\\n\\n`VERDICT: APPROVED`\\n\\nor\\n\\n`VERDICT: REJECTED`\\n\\nReturn valid JSON only, no markdown fences:\\n{\\\"verdict\\\":\\\"APPROVE\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.0,\\\"covered\\\":[\\\"spec_lab\\\",\\\"boilerplate_reuse\\\",\\\"ios_quality\\\",\\\"appium_qa\\\",\\\"mobbin_safety\\\",\\\"release_hardening\\\"],\\\"gaps\\\":[]}\\n\",\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/evals/promptfoo-output.json:118:          \"label\": \"Evaluate whether this iPhone App Factory prompt suite is strong enough for overnight agentic app generation.\\n\\nPrompt registry:\\n{{prompt_registry}}\\n\\nGolden cases:\\n{{golden_cases}}\\n\\nRepresentative prompts:\\nSPEC_CONSENSUS:\\n{{spec_consensus}}\\n\\nARCHITECTURE:\\n{{architecture_consensus}}\\n\\nIMPLEMENT_INTEGRATION:\\n{{implement_integration}}\\n\\nAI_UI_EXPLORER:\\n{{ai_ui_explorer}}\\n\\nFINAL_CONSENSUS:\\n{{final_consensus}}\\n\\nReturn valid JSON only, no markdown fences:\\n{\\\"verdict\\\":\\\"APPROVE\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.0,\\\"covered\\\":[\\\"spec_lab\\\",\\\"boilerplate_reuse\\\",\\\"ios_quality\\\",\\\"appium_qa\\\",\\\"mobbin_safety\\\",\\\"release_hardening\\\"],\\\"gaps\\\":[]}\\n\",\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/evals/promptfoo-output.json:137:          \"output\": \"# Evaluation: iPhone App Factory Prompt Suite\\n\\n## Overall Assessment: **STRONG BUT WITH CRITICAL GAPS** (7.2/10)\\n\\nThis is a well-architected prompt suite with excellent structural discipline, but it has **three blocking vulnerabilities** for overnight agentic execution.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Strengths ✅\\n\\n| Category | Evidence |\\n|----------|----------|\\n| **Workflow coherence** | Clear stage progression (research → spec → architecture → implementation → review → release) |\\n| **Spec lab rigor** | Independent candidates + adversarial critique + red team + consensus pattern is sound |\\n| **Boilerplate enforcement** | Multiple checkpoints (spec, architecture, implementation, review) bias toward reuse |\\n| **Quality gates** | Explicit xcodebuild, SwiftLint, SwiftFormat, Qlty, Appium requirements |\\n| **Verdict discipline** | Binary APPROVED/REJECTED verdicts with blocking rules prevent ambiguous handoffs |\\n| **Secret handling intent** | \\\"Never print environment variables\\\" appears 6+ times |\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Critical Gaps ❌\\n\\n### 1. **Secret Handling is Underspecified** (BLOCKING)\\n\\n**Problem:**\\n- `research-design-patterns.md` must_include lists `MOBBIN_EMAIL`, `MOBBIN_PASSWORD` but no prompt shows *how* to use them safely\\n- `implement-foundation.md` mentions \\\"secrets\\\" but doesn't specify injection mechanism\\n- No prompt explicitly forbids `os.environ.dump()`, `print(os.environ)`, or credential logging in agent outputs\\n- No prompt specifies redaction rules for CI logs\\n\\n**Risk:** Overnight agent could leak credentials to stdout/logs during research or implementation phases.\\n\\n**Required fix:**\\n```yaml\\nmust_include: [\\n  \\\"never print environment variables\\\",\\n  \\\"use getenv() with redaction wrapper\\\",\\n  \\\"credential verification: true/false only\\\",\\n  \\\"no credential values in logs or reports\\\",\\n  \\\"sanitize all JSON outputs for secrets\\\"\\n]\\n```\\n\\n### 2. **Appium/XCUITest Evidence is Optional** (BLOCKING FOR OVERNIGHT)\\n\\n**Problem:**\\n- `ai-ui-explorer.md` says \\\"Do not mark the pass complete unless a real simulator/Appium run happened, **unless the workflow explicitly allows macOS deferral**\\\"\\n- `final-consensus.md` says \\\"If macOS/Xcode or Appium evidence is missing **and not explicitly deferred**, reject\\\"\\n- No prompt defines what \\\"explicitly deferred\\\" means or under what conditions it's acceptable\\n- Overnight execution on headless CI likely cannot run iOS simulator → creates escape hatch for skipping QA\\n\\n**Risk:** Agent defers Appium, skips real device testing, ships untested app.\\n\\n**Required fix:**\\n```yaml\\n# In final-consensus.md\\nRules:\\n  - Appium deferral only allowed if:\\n    1. Workflow input explicitly sets \\\"defer_appium: true\\\"\\n    2. A blocking issue prevents simulator setup (documented)\",\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/evals/promptfoo-output.json:158:            \"architecture_consensus\": \"file://../../prompts/iphone-app-factory/architecture-consensus.md\",\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/evals/promptfoo-output.json:198:          \"architecture_consensus\": \"file://../../prompts/iphone-app-factory/architecture-consensus.md\",\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/evals/promptfoo-output.json:249:      \"Evaluate whether this iPhone App Factory prompt suite is strong enough for overnight agentic app generation.\\n\\nPrompt registry:\\n{{prompt_registry}}\\n\\nGolden cases:\\n{{golden_cases}}\\n\\nRepresentative prompts:\\nSPEC_CONSENSUS:\\n{{spec_consensus}}\\n\\nARCHITECTURE:\\n{{architecture_consensus}}\\n\\nIMPLEMENT_INTEGRATION:\\n{{implement_integration}}\\n\\nAI_UI_EXPLORER:\\n{{ai_ui_explorer}}\\n\\nFINAL_CONSENSUS:\\n{{final_consensus}}\\n\\nReturn valid JSON only, no markdown fences:\\n{\\\"verdict\\\":\\\"APPROVE\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.0,\\\"covered\\\":[\\\"spec_lab\\\",\\\"boilerplate_reuse\\\",\\\"ios_quality\\\",\\\"appium_qa\\\",\\\"mobbin_safety\\\",\\\"release_hardening\\\"],\\\"gaps\\\":[]}\\n\"\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/evals/promptfoo-output.json:269:          \"architecture_consensus\": \"file://../../prompts/iphone-app-factory/architecture-consensus.md\",\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/quality-bar.json:21:    \"final review fanout must approve product fidelity, iOS architecture, security, quality, QA, and release readiness\"\nprompts/iphone-app-factory/implement-foundation.md:5:Read the spec, definition of done, architecture, ADR, and quality bar.\nprompts/iphone-app-factory/final-consensus.md:8:- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/reviews/ios-architecture.md`\nprompts/iphone-app-factory/boilerplate-setup.md:6:- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture.md`\nprompts/iphone-app-factory/architecture-consensus.md:7:- all architecture candidates in context\nprompts/iphone-app-factory/architecture-consensus.md:12:- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture.md`\nprompts/iphone-app-factory/architecture-consensus.md:15:The architecture must explicitly map the product to SwiftAIBoilerplatePro:\nprompts/iphone-app-factory/architecture-candidate.md:10:Create an architecture plan that extends SwiftAIBoilerplatePro instead of rebuilding it.\nprompts/iphone-app-factory/architecture-candidate.md:26:Write the architecture candidate in your response with a clear model identity.\nprompts/iphone-app-factory/app-store-hardening.md:6:- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture.md`\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
