onalization surfaces only; never required for alarm firing, dismissal, fallback, or wake verification.\n- `Packages/FeatureSettings`\n  - Hosts alarm defaults, strictness profiles (weekday/weekend/travel), permission recovery affordances, and tone/policy options.\n- `Packages/Localization`\n  - Owns all user-facing strings, including App Store 4.3 differentiation language and anti-\"guaranteed wake\" constraints.\n- `Packages/DesignSystem`\n  - Implements 3:30am-safe components (large targets, high contrast, low cognitive load), avoiding ad-like clutter.\n- `CompositionRoot`\n  - Registers implementations for mission engine, fallback resolver, wake-check scheduler, reliability logger, and screen entry points.\n\n## WakeTask Feature Slices\n1. Alarm Setup Slice\n- Configure alarm + mission chain.\n- Validate mission inputs at setup (scan target pre-validation, camera permission checks).\n\n2. Alarm Execution Slice\n- Fire alarm locally.\n- Enforce mission-gated dismissal (math, memory, motion, scan).\n- Route to fallback mission in one step on unavailable/invalid primary mission conditions.\n\n3. Post-dismiss Verification Slice\n- Schedule wake checks at +3, +7, +12 minutes from dismissal time.\n- Escalate via re-alarm on missed/failed checks.\n- Mark session successful only if all required checks pass.\n\n4. Trust & Review Slice\n- Render morning timeline from persisted reliability fields.\n- Expose fallback usage and profile used for trust transparency.\n\n## Dependency Direction\n1. `DesignSystem`/`Localization` are leaf presentation dependencies.\n2. `FeatureSettings` and WakeTask feature UIs depend on `Core` protocols and DesignSystem.\n3. Repository implementations depend on `Storage` and optionally `Networking`.\n4. Monetization/auth adapters depend on `Payments`/`Auth` but never invert into `Core`.\n5. `CompositionRoot` performs final assembly and injects protocols into app entry points.\n\n## Concurrency and Reliability Constraints\n- Isolate alarm-state mutation behind actor-backed services.\n- Use main-actor view models and async protocol APIs for mission evaluation and wake checks.\n- Keep mission and wake-check scheduling deterministic and resumable after app relaunch.\n- Ensure fallback routing cannot dead-end by requiring an always-available fallback mission type.\n\n## Testing and Evidence Plan\n- Unit tests: mission validators, fallback resolver, wake-check scheduler timing, reliability timeline mapping.\n- Integration tests: full dismissal->wake-check escalation path and permission denial recovery.\n- UI tests/Appium exploratory: tap every reachable enabled control, include trust log/profile switching routes.\n- Blocking quality gates: `xcodebuild build`, `xcodebuild test`, SwiftLint, SwiftFormat, Qlty, secret scan, App Store string audit.\n\n## Non-goals Guardrail\n- No rebuild of Auth/Payments/AI/Networking/Storage/Localization/DesignSystem/CompositionRoot.\n- No sleep-stage analytics platform, social wake community, or wearable-required core logic in MVP.\nEOF'","aggregated_output":"","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
